

git pull origin main

This script automatically pulls the latest code from a GitHub repository.

Why this is used in real companies:--
In real DevOps workflows:
Code changes are pushed to GitHub
Servers need the latest code
Pulling manually is error-prone
This script is used in:
Deployment pipeline
CI/CD servers
Cron jobs
Webhook trigger.


#!/bin/bash

# -----------------------------
# Git Repository Auto Pull Script
# -----------------------------
# This script pulls latest code from GitHub
# Used in deployment automation

# --------- Variables ---------
REPO_DIR="/home/ubuntu/myapp"
BRANCH="main"

# --------- Go to Repo Directory ---------
cd "$REPO_DIR" || {
  echo "❌ Directory not found: $REPO_DIR"
  exit 1
}

# --------- Check Git Repository ---------
if [ -d ".git" ]; then
    echo "Git repository found"
else
    echo "❌ Not a Git repository"
    exit 1
fi

# --------- Pull Latest Code ---------
if git pull origin "$BRANCH"; then
    echo "✅ Code pulled successfully"
else
    echo "❌ Git pull failed"
fi
